<section>
<title>Test negative widths</title>
<para>
This is a test for a font some of whose characters have negative widths, that 
is, they move the printing position backwards. The PMW-Music font has some such 
characters, for moving around when composing non-simple graphics. Here is an 
example that uses it:
</para>
<literallayout>
&nbsp;
<emphasis role="PMW-Music/10">FFyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy#x~&#x27;~</emphasis><emphasis role="bold">3</emphasis><emphasis role="PMW-Music/10">yyyyyyww</emphasis><emphasis role="bold">4  </emphasis><emphasis role="PMW-Music/10">B{@{xIx~8}}~8}}wwww|=5}}=5}~xxIw{@{B</emphasis>
&nbsp;
</literallayout>
<para>
There was a bug in SDoP that gave a spurious `unknown character' error for that 
example.
</para>
<sect1>
<title>Subsection title</title>
<para>
This is a subsection, to test changing the title font.
</para>
</sect1>
<para>
